{
  "abstract": "In a crop rotation experiment, paddy and sorghum sown in the kharif reduced the lentil wilt in the succeeding rabi. In the same treatments higher grain yields were also recorded. Comparatively low incidence of wilt was recorded in December 15 planting than the earlier plantings",
